The House Price Prediction project was completed using Linear Regression and Random Forest Regressor models. After cleaning and encoding the data, both models were trained and evaluated. Random Forest achieved better performance with a higher R² score and lower prediction error. The most influential features were area, bathrooms, stories, and parking availability. The dataset showed that larger houses with more amenities generally have higher prices. Based on the results, real estate businesses should focus on these key property characteristics when estimating house values.